-- Edinburgh Beats Munster in Heineken Cup Rugby as Scarlets Win
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-12T18:57:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-12/edinburgh-beats-munster-in-heineken-cup-rugby-as-scarlets-win.html
Edinburgh beat Munster 29-23 in
their Heineken Cup rugby opener, while the Scarlets outscored
Harlequins 33-26.  Greig Laidlaw kicked 19 points and Matthew Scott and Tim
Visser scored tries in Edinburgh’s home win over the two-time
champion. Rhys Priestland booted 18 points in the Scarlets’
victory in London.  In other matches on the first weekend of European rugby’s
elite club competition, Castres beat Northampston Saints 19-13,
Montpelier won 27-10 at Treviso, three-time champions Leinster
beat the Ospreys 19-9, and Gloucester beat Perpignan 27-22.  Toulon opens defense of its title tomorrow against  Glasgow
Warriors , while Clermont Auvergne visits Racing Metro and the
Exeter Chiefs host  Cardiff Blues . Record four-time champion
Toulouse routed Zebre 38-5, Saracens beat Connacht 23-17 and
Ulster beat Leicester Tigers 22-16 in last night’s matches.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
